comments[7]{created_at,author,text}:
  "2026-07-13T18:17:05.362Z",codex-root,"Progress evidence: privacy-minimal derived usage ledger, propensity logging, central mutation-touch capture, decayed affinity scorer signal, retention/opt-out controls, and focused 79-test suite green."
  "2026-07-13T19:55:49.495Z",codex-root,"Completion evidence: delivered a privacy-minimal workspace-local derived JSONL ledger with bounded retention/compaction, zero-I/O opt-out, propensity rows (profile/rank/inclusion), inline context/next serving, get/claim/mutation/close touches, per-author decay and exploration floor, usage_affinity scorer explanations, and core-only post-command capture. The committed pm-atfm corpus now includes served-then-used versus served-and-ignored and proves the used item ranks first while unseen exploration candidates remain; all five scenarios score 1.0 on NDCG, reciprocal rank, required recall, continuity, and token adherence. Focused 82-test linked suite passes; shared full suite passes 5,623 tests at exact 100/100/100/100; package-first dogfood passed 88 commands; fresh manual and packed-SDK temp acceptance passed. GitHub security/dependency and live Sentry/release findings were appended to canonical pm-qwoy, pm-7zs0, pm-wfvq, and pm-ksv2 without duplicate items or claims."
  "2026-07-13T20:19:42.913Z",codex-root,"Review convergence evidence: multi-item touches now validate once, append once, and compact once instead of repeated append/read/rename cycles; compaction temp names use process id plus random UUID; affinity normalization guards complete decay underflow; central mutations use configured default author. Regression coverage proves batch retention, underflow exploration floor, and an actual configured-author central mutation ledger row. Exact 100/100/100/100 coverage and all quality/context/dogfood gates pass."
  "2026-07-13T20:20:25.184Z",codex-root,"Post-review manual acceptance: fresh project /tmp/pm-review-acceptance-WllJCA initialized and configured entirely through the built CLI with author-default=configured-agent; context serving followed by update of pm-gq6a produced a mutation touch with author configured-agent and intent update in the derived ledger while PM_AUTHOR was unset."
  "2026-07-13T20:46:41.645Z",codex-review-loop-agent,"Second review convergence evidence: accepted Gemini zero-I/O and timestamp hot-path findings plus Greptile concurrent-compaction finding. Disabled feedback now returns before settings reads and all public ledger entrypoints; touch timestamps are parsed once; every writer holds the shared context-usage ledger lock across append and optional compaction. An 8-writer compaction regression preserves all event ids. Full suite passes 281 files / 5,628 tests at exact 100% statements 35,814/35,814, branches 25,688/25,688, functions 7,244/7,244, lines 35,009/35,009; lint, zero-clone, static, package-boundary, token-budget, and five-scenario context quality gates pass."
  "2026-07-13T21:02:18.482Z",codex-review-loop-agent,"Third review convergence evidence: accepted normalized touch-id deduplication and runtime validation, Node-native UTF-8 byte estimation, and pagination over the full ranked active set before token packing. Added regressions for duplicate/non-string touch ids and large multibyte identities across cursor pages. Declined the proposed unique lock-owner change because acquireLock uses exclusive O_EXCL lock-file creation and owner is diagnostic metadata only, so same-process callers cannot re-enter. Focused 52 tests, full 5,630-test exact 100% coverage (35,828 statements, 25,690 branches, 7,250 functions, 35,022 lines), ESLint, static quality, package boundary, token budget, and five-scenario context eval pass."
  "2026-07-13T21:10:07.407Z",codex-review-loop-agent,"Final review convergence evidence: the complete thread-aware inventory surfaced Greptile's auto-resolved ready-queue P1, so it was handled despite not appearing in the unresolved subset. pm next now preserves the complete scorer-ranked ready queue for recommendation, ready count, and in-progress semantics while retaining token packing for bounded accounting and propensity disclosure. A large multibyte-identity regression proves three ready items remain semantically visible when the packer omits identities. Full suite passes 281 files / 5,631 tests at exact 100% statements 35,828/35,828, branches 25,690/25,690, functions 7,250/7,250, lines 35,022/35,022; focused 73 tests, ESLint, static quality, package boundary, token budget, and context eval pass."
