close_reason: Derived context usage feedback is implemented and fully verified.
body: "The pm-vvib cognitive ADR maps seven memory subsystems onto pm primitives, but omits the one mechanism that makes biological memory adaptive: retrieval strengthens the trace. Every signal in pm-4k6b's current design (recency, graph proximity, priority, semantics, knowledge density, author affinity) describes the workspace; none observes whether the context the engine served was actually useful. Without outcome feedback the scorer can be tuned once (pm-atfm golden judgments) but never learns from live use.\n\nProposal: when pm context/next serve a working set, record a minimal serving event; when the same author subsequently gets/claims/updates/closes a served item within a horizon, that pairing becomes an implicit positive judgment. Aggregated (and decayed) per item and per (author, item), it becomes: (1) a usage-affinity input to the pm-4k6b scorer — items this agent historically acted on after being shown rank higher for this agent; (2) free implicit-judgment data for the pm-atfm harness, complementing hand-graded goldens; (3) at pm-5qmm consolidation time, a salience hint for what an epoch rollup should keep verbatim vs summarize away.\n\nCognitive framing (extends pm-vvib, to be added to the ADR's subsystem map if accepted): retrieval-practice / Hebbian strengthening — recall is not read-only; it reshapes future recall. Graceful-forgetting decay already in the ADR is the complementary weakening term.\n\nSequencing: phase 2+ of the context engine — needs pm-3hps (feature store) and the pm-h3no scorer contract landed first; the ledger design should ride the same derived-store mechanics as pm-3hps. Priority 3 until pm-4k6b core ships a deterministic baseline (determinism note: usage signal is itself deterministic for a fixed ledger state, preserving pm-4k6b's reproducibility AC).\n\nDuplicate-check evidence: pm search 'context usage feedback signal reinforcement' -> only pm-4k6b (scorer, no outcome loop) and unrelated closed items; pm-vvib body confirms no strengthening-through-recall subsystem exists in the recorded architecture."
